rounds.response:
I see the board now:

 X | 1 | O 
---+---+---
 O | O | 5 
---+---+---
 X | 7 | 8 

If I don’t act immediately, Player 0 can win next turn by playing 5 to complete the middle row (3–4–5 would become O-O-O).  
Only two safe moves truly block that immediate threat: [1] or [5].  
If I pick [5], the board would still look dangerous and leave other winning lines open, whereas [1] both blocks the row and starts my diagonal X-X-X threat (cells 0-1-2).  
So I’ll seize cell 1:

[1]
